===English===
==Noun phrase==
'''[[comic]] [[book]]'''
#a [[book]] or [[magazine]] that uses images in a juxtaposed sequence to tell a [[story]] or [[series]] of stories, primarily in serialized form, usually fiction

==Usage note==
Although the name [[comic book]] implies that humor is involved, not all '''comic books''' are funny.  Oftentimes people associate '''comic books''' with adventure stories involving [[superhero]]es.